B<U+00E9>la married Helena of Rascia upon the initiation of his cousin, King Stephen II at the beginning of 1129.{{sfn|Makk|1994|p=281}} Helena was a daughter of [[Uro<U+0161> I of Rascia]] and his wife [[Anna Diogenissa|Anna]], whose origin is uncertain.{{sfn|Makk|1994|p=281}} Queen Helena gave birth to at least six children.{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|p=173}} The first of these, the future King [[G<U+00E9>za II of Hungary]], was born in 1130.{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|p=Appendix 3}} Three brothers{{mdash}}[[Ladislaus II of Hungary|Ladislaus]], [[Stephen IV of Hungary|Stephen]] and <U+00C1>lmos{{mdash}}were born in the early 1130s.{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|p=Appendix 3}} Sophia, the first daughter of the royal couple, was born around 1135; she died as a nun in [[Admont Abbey]] after her engagement with Henry Berengar of Germany was broken.{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|pp=177, Appendix 3}} B<U+00E9>la II's youngest daughter [[Elisabeth of Hungary (1128<U+2013>1154)|Gertrud]], who was born in about 1140, married [[Mieszko III the Old|Mieszko III of Poland]].{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|pp=173, Appendix 3}}

The following family tree presents B<U+00E9>la's ancestors and some of his relatives who are mentioned in the article.{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|p=Appendix 2}}
